13/06/2007
BRUSSELS, Belgium -- German Foreign Minister Frank-Walter Steinmeier, whose country currently holds the rotating EU presidency, confirmed on Tuesday (June 12th) that efforts to free five Bulgarian nurses and a Palestinian doctor on death row in Libya would continue.
Steinmeier was speaking in Brussels after returning from Libya, accompanied by EU Commissioner for External Relations Benita Ferrero-Waldner.
He said extensive talks were held with the Libyan side regarding the medics, who were convicted in a controversial HIV infection case.
(Monitor - BNR, BTA - 12/06/07)
